<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="least-pron">least <strong><em>pron</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /liːst/    美 /liːst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-the">1.★ <strong>[常与the连用] 最少；最小：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Price is <strong>the least of my concerns</strong>. 
我一点儿都不关心价格。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could take you to the office for your interview. <strong>It's the least I could do</strong>.
我可以送你去公司面试，这是我起码可以做的事。</p><footer>2013 山东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="at-the-least">at (the) least</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>(数量上) 不少于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I need at least five days to complete the task. 
我至少需要5天时间来完成这项任务。</p><footer>译林② – 3</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>至少；起码：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A good friend is willing to offer the help which you need, or can at least give you some advice. 
一个好朋友愿意在你需要时提供帮助，或者至少可以给你一些建议。</p><footer> 2010 重庆</footer></div>

<h3 id="not-in-the-least-not-the-least-bit">not in the least / not the least (bit)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>一点儿也不 (not at all)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I didn't know his name or the least bit about him.
我不知道他的名字，或者说一点儿也不了解他。</p><footer>2006 湖北</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The house still needed a lot of work, but <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (起码) the kitchen was fi nished.  （2008 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. at least  </p></div>